The paper deals with lossy compression of individual sequences using finite-state encoders and decoders, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of finite-state machines also suggests a connection to the field of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of block codes, which is a topic related to machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The concept of universal codes is also mentioned, which is a topic related to signal processing and information theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the results to multimedia compression, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
